headline: How the Story Surrounding Cummins Is Evolving as Analysts Adjust to New Growth Drivers
summary: Analysts have modestly raised their fair value estimate for Cummins, increasing the price target from $431.98 to $444.74. This adjustment reflects a combination of renewed optimism and prudent caution as Wall Street considers stronger demand outlooks, improved operational trends, and the influence of rising interest in artificial intelligence.
